description:
The javadoc for constructor Image(Device, ImageData) needs to be updated due to a bug. The current javadoc does not mention that an exception is thrown when using certain types of invalid ImageData. Here is an example code snippet that triggers the issue:

import org.eclipse.swt.widgets.*;

public class TestImageInvalidImage {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        ImageData data = new ImageData(10, 10, 1, new PaletteData(0xff0000, 0x00ff00, 0x0000ff));
        Image image = new Image(Display.getDefault(), data);
        // image.dispose();
    }
}
